183 /*
184  * catcls_allocate_entry () -
185  * return:
186  * thread_p(in):
187  */
188 static CATCLS_ENTRY *
189 catcls_allocate_entry (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p)
190 {
191  CATCLS_ENTRY *entry_p;
192 
193  assert (csect_check_own (thread_p, CSECT_CT_OID_TABLE) == 1);
194 
195  if (catcls_Free_entry_list != NULL)
196  {
197  entry_p = catcls_Free_entry_list;
198  catcls_Free_entry_list = catcls_Free_entry_list->next;
199  }
200  else
201  {
202  entry_p = (CATCLS_ENTRY *) malloc (sizeof (CATCLS_ENTRY));
203  if (entry_p == NULL)
204  {
205  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, sizeof (CATCLS_ENTRY));
206  return NULL;
207  }
208  }
209 
210  entry_p->next = NULL;
211  return entry_p;
212 }

214 /*
215  * catcls_free_entry_kv () - A callback function to free memory
216  * allocated for a catcls entry.
217  * return:
218  * key(in):
219  * data(in):
220  * args(in):
221  */
222 static int
223 catcls_free_entry_kv (const void *key, void *data, void *args)
224 {
225  return catcls_free_entry ((CATCLS_ENTRY *) data);
226 }

228 /*
229  * catcls_free_entry () - free memory allocated for a catcls entry.
230  * return:
231  * entry_p(in)
232  */
233 static int
234 catcls_free_entry (CATCLS_ENTRY * entry_p)
235 {
236  assert (csect_check_own (NULL, CSECT_CT_OID_TABLE) == 1);
237 
238  entry_p->next = catcls_Free_entry_list;
239  catcls_Free_entry_list = entry_p;
240 
241  return NO_ERROR;
242 }

244 /*
245  * catcls_initialize_class_oid_to_oid_hash_table () -
246  * return:
247  * thread_p(in):
248  * num_entry(in):
249  */
250 static int
251 catcls_initialize_class_oid_to_oid_hash_table (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, int num_entry)
252 {
253  if (csect_enter (thread_p, CSECT_CT_OID_TABLE, INF_WAIT) != NO_ERROR)
254  {
255  return ER_FAILED;
256  }
257 
258  catcls_Class_oid_to_oid_hash_table = mht_create ("Class OID to OID", num_entry, oid_hash, oid_compare_equals);
259 
260  if (catcls_Class_oid_to_oid_hash_table == NULL)
261  {
262  csect_exit (thread_p, CSECT_CT_OID_TABLE);
263  return ER_FAILED;
264  }
265 
266  csect_exit (thread_p, CSECT_CT_OID_TABLE);
267 
268  return NO_ERROR;
269 }
270 
271 /*
272  * catcls_finalize_class_oid_to_oid_hash_table () -
273  * return:
274  * thread_p(in):
275  */
276 int
277 catcls_finalize_class_oid_to_oid_hash_table (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p)
278 {
279  CATCLS_ENTRY *entry_p, *next_p;
280 
281  if (csect_enter (thread_p, CSECT_CT_OID_TABLE, INF_WAIT) != NO_ERROR)
282  {
283  return ER_FAILED;
284  }
285 
286  if (catcls_Class_oid_to_oid_hash_table)
287  {
288  mht_map (catcls_Class_oid_to_oid_hash_table, catcls_free_entry_kv, NULL);
289  mht_destroy (catcls_Class_oid_to_oid_hash_table);
290  }
291 
292  for (entry_p = catcls_Free_entry_list; entry_p; entry_p = next_p)
293  {
294  next_p = entry_p->next;
295  free_and_init (entry_p);
296  }
297  catcls_Free_entry_list = NULL;
298  catcls_Class_oid_to_oid_hash_table = NULL;
299 
300  csect_exit (thread_p, CSECT_CT_OID_TABLE);
301 
302  return NO_ERROR;
303 }

305 /*
306  * catcls_find_oid () -
307  * return:
308  * thread_p(in):
309  * class_oid(in):
310  */
311 static OID *
312 catcls_find_oid (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, OID * class_oid_p)
313 {
314  CATCLS_ENTRY *entry_p;
315 
316 #if defined (SERVER_MODE)
317  assert (csect_check_own (thread_p, CSECT_CT_OID_TABLE) == 2);
318 #endif
319 
320  if (catcls_Class_oid_to_oid_hash_table)
321  {
322  entry_p = (CATCLS_ENTRY *) mht_get (catcls_Class_oid_to_oid_hash_table, (void *) class_oid_p);
323  if (entry_p != NULL)
324  {
325  return &entry_p->oid;
326  }
327  else
328  {
329  return NULL;
330  }
331  }
332 
333  return NULL;
334 }

336 /*
337  * catcls_put_entry () -
338  * return:
339  * thread_p(in):
340  * entry(in):
341  * already_exists(out):
342  */
343 static int
344 catcls_put_entry (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, CATCLS_ENTRY * entry_p, bool * already_exists)
345 {
346  const CATCLS_ENTRY *val_p = NULL;
347  *already_exists = true;
348 
349  assert (csect_check_own (thread_p, CSECT_CT_OID_TABLE) == 1);
350 
351  if (catcls_Class_oid_to_oid_hash_table)
352  {
353  val_p =
354  (const CATCLS_ENTRY *) mht_put_if_not_exists (catcls_Class_oid_to_oid_hash_table, &entry_p->class_oid, entry_p);
355  if (val_p == NULL)
356  {
357  return ER_FAILED;
358  }
359 
360  if ((void *) val_p != (void *) entry_p)
361  {
362  assert (OID_EQ (&val_p->class_oid, &entry_p->class_oid));
363  assert (OID_EQ (&val_p->oid, &entry_p->oid));
364  *already_exists = true;
365  }
366  else
367  {
368  *already_exists = false;
369  }
370  }
371 
372  return NO_ERROR;
373 }

436 /*
437  * catcls_allocate_or_value () -
438  * return:
439  * size(in):
440  */
441 static OR_VALUE *
442 catcls_allocate_or_value (int size)
443 {
444  OR_VALUE *value_p;
445  int i;
446  size_t msize;
447 
448  msize = size * sizeof (OR_VALUE);
449  value_p = (OR_VALUE *) malloc (msize);
450  if (value_p == NULL)
451  {
452  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, msize);
453  }
454  else
455  {
456  for (i = 0; i < size; i++)
457  {
458  db_value_put_null (&value_p[i].value);
459  value_p[i].sub.value = NULL;
460  value_p[i].sub.count = -1;
461  }
462  }
463 
464  return (value_p);
465 }

473 static void
474 catcls_free_sub_value (OR_VALUE * values, int count)

484  }
485  free_and_init (values);

487 }

505 /*
506  * catcls_expand_or_value_by_def () -
507  * return:
508  * value(in):
509  * def(in):
510  */
511 static int
512 catcls_expand_or_value_by_def (OR_VALUE * value_p, CT_CLASS * def_p)
513 {
514  OR_VALUE *attrs_p;
515  int n_attrs;
516  CT_ATTR *att_def_p;
517  int i;
518  int error;
519 
520  if (value_p != NULL)
521  {
522  /* index_of */
523  COPY_OID (&value_p->id.classoid, &def_p->cc_classoid);
524 
525  n_attrs = def_p->cc_n_atts;
526  attrs_p = catcls_allocate_or_value (n_attrs);
527  if (attrs_p == NULL)
528  {
529  return ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
530  }
531 
532  value_p->sub.value = attrs_p;
533  value_p->sub.count = n_attrs;
534 
535  att_def_p = def_p->cc_atts;
536  for (i = 0; i < n_attrs; i++)
537  {
538  attrs_p[i].id.attrid = att_def_p[i].ca_id;
539  error =
540  db_value_domain_init (&attrs_p[i].value, att_def_p[i].ca_type, DB_DEFAULT_PRECISION, DB_DEFAULT_SCALE);
541  if (error != NO_ERROR)
542  {
543  return error;
544  }
545  }
546  }
547 
548  return NO_ERROR;
549 }

551 /*
552  * catcls_guess_record_length () -
553  * return:
554  * value(in):
555  */
556 static int
557 catcls_guess_record_length (OR_VALUE * value_p)
558 {
559  int length;
560  DB_TYPE data_type;
561  PR_TYPE *map_p;
562  OR_VALUE *attrs_p;
563  int n_attrs, i;
564 
565  attrs_p = value_p->sub.value;
566  n_attrs = value_p->sub.count;
567 
568  length = OR_MVCC_MAX_HEADER_SIZE + OR_VAR_TABLE_SIZE (n_attrs) + OR_BOUND_BIT_BYTES (n_attrs);
569 
570  for (i = 0; i < n_attrs; i++)
571  {
572  data_type = DB_VALUE_DOMAIN_TYPE (&attrs_p[i].value);
573  map_p = tp_Type_id_map[data_type];
574 
575  if (map_p->data_lengthval != NULL)
576  {
577  length += (*(map_p->data_lengthval)) (&attrs_p[i].value, 1);
578  }
579  else if (map_p->disksize)
580  {
581  length += map_p->disksize;
582  }
583  /* else : is null-type */
584  }
585 
586  return (length);
587 }

589 /*
590  * catcls_find_class_oid_by_class_name () -
591  * return:
592  * name(in):
593  * class_oid(in):
594  */
595 static int
596 catcls_find_class_oid_by_class_name (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const char *name_p, OID * class_oid_p)
597 {
598  LC_FIND_CLASSNAME status;
599 
600  status = xlocator_find_class_oid (thread_p, name_p, class_oid_p, NULL_LOCK);
601 
602  if (status == LC_CLASSNAME_ERROR)
603  {
604  er_set (ER_WARNING_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_LC_UNKNOWN_CLASSNAME, 1, name_p);
605  return ER_FAILED;
606  }
607  else if (status == LC_CLASSNAME_DELETED)
608  {
609  /* not found the class */
610  OID_SET_NULL (class_oid_p);
611  }
612 
613  return NO_ERROR;

680 /*

682  * index for classname

688 catcls_find_oid_by_class_name (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const char *name_p, OID * oid_p)

697  {
698  return error;

718 /*
719  * catcls_convert_class_oid_to_oid () -
720  * return:
721  * oid_val(in):
722  */
723 static int
724 catcls_convert_class_oid_to_oid (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, DB_VALUE * oid_val_p)
725 {
726  char *name_p = NULL;
727  OID oid_buf;
728  OID *class_oid_p, *oid_p;
729  CATCLS_ENTRY *entry_p;
730  bool already_exists;
731 
732  if (DB_IS_NULL (oid_val_p))
733  {
734  return NO_ERROR;
735  }
736 
737  class_oid_p = db_get_oid (oid_val_p);
738 
739  if (csect_enter_as_reader (thread_p, CSECT_CT_OID_TABLE, INF_WAIT) != NO_ERROR)
740  {
741  return ER_FAILED;
742  }
743 
744  oid_p = catcls_find_oid (thread_p, class_oid_p);
745 
746  csect_exit (thread_p, CSECT_CT_OID_TABLE);
747 
748  if (oid_p == NULL)
749  {
750  oid_p = &oid_buf;
751  if (heap_get_class_name (thread_p, class_oid_p, &name_p) != NO_ERROR)
752  {
753  /* class_oid object may be deleted */
754  ASSERT_ERROR ();
755  db_make_null (oid_val_p);
756 
757  return er_errid ();
758  }
759 
760  if (name_p == NULL)
761  {
762  /* this is only possible if ER_HEAP_NODATA_NEWADDRESS occur */
763  db_make_null (oid_val_p);
764  return NO_ERROR;
765  }
766 
767  if (catcls_find_oid_by_class_name (thread_p, name_p, oid_p) != NO_ERROR)
768  {
769  free_and_init (name_p);
770 
771  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
772  return er_errid ();
773  }
774 
775  if (!OID_ISNULL (oid_p))
776  {
777  if (csect_enter (thread_p, CSECT_CT_OID_TABLE, INF_WAIT) != NO_ERROR)
778  {
779  return ER_FAILED;
780  }
781 
782  if ((entry_p = catcls_allocate_entry (thread_p)) != NULL)
783  {
784  COPY_OID (&entry_p->class_oid, class_oid_p);
785  COPY_OID (&entry_p->oid, oid_p);
786  catcls_put_entry (thread_p, entry_p, &already_exists);
787  /* if it already exists, just free current entry_p */
788  if (already_exists)
789  {
790  catcls_free_entry (entry_p);
791  }
792  }
793 
794  csect_exit (thread_p, CSECT_CT_OID_TABLE);
795  }
796  }
797 
798  db_make_oid (oid_val_p, oid_p);
799 
800  if (name_p)
801  {
802  free_and_init (name_p);
803  }
804 
805  return NO_ERROR;
806 }

808 /*
809  * catcls_convert_attr_id_to_name () -
810  * return:
811  * obuf(in):
812  * value(in):
813  */
814 static int
815 catcls_convert_attr_id_to_name (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, OR_BUF * orbuf_p, OR_VALUE * value_p)
816 {
817  OR_BUF *buf_p, orep;
818  OR_VALUE *indexes, *keys;
819  OR_VALUE *index_atts, *key_atts;
820  OR_VALUE *id_val_p = NULL, *id_atts;
821  OR_VALUE *ids;
822  OR_VARINFO *vars = NULL;
823  int id;
824  int size;
825  int i, j, k;
826  int error = NO_ERROR;
827 
828  buf_p = &orep;
829  or_init (buf_p, orbuf_p->buffer, (int) (orbuf_p->endptr - orbuf_p->buffer));
830 
831  or_advance (buf_p, OR_NON_MVCC_HEADER_SIZE);
832 
833  size = tf_Metaclass_class.mc_n_variable;
834  vars = or_get_var_table (buf_p, size, catcls_unpack_allocator);
835  if (vars == NULL)
836  {
837  size_t msize = size * sizeof (OR_VARINFO);
838  error = ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
839  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, error, 1, msize);
840 
841  return error;
842  }
843 
844  /* jump to the 'attributes' and extract its id/name. there are no indexes for shared or class attributes, so we need
845  * only id/name for 'attributes'. the offsets are relative to end of the class record header */
846  or_seek (buf_p, vars[ORC_ATTRIBUTES_INDEX].offset + OR_NON_MVCC_HEADER_SIZE);
847 
848  id_val_p = catcls_allocate_or_value (1);
849  if (id_val_p == NULL)
850  {
851  free_and_init (vars);
852  return ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
853  }
854 
855  error =
856  catcls_get_subset (thread_p, buf_p, vars[ORC_ATTRIBUTES_INDEX].length, id_val_p, catcls_get_or_value_from_attrid);
857  if (error != NO_ERROR)
858  {
859  free_and_init (vars);
860  free_and_init (id_val_p);
861  return error;
862  }
863 
864  /* replace id with name for each key attribute */
865  for (indexes = value_p->sub.value, i = 0; i < value_p->sub.count; i++)
866  {
867  index_atts = indexes[i].sub.value;
868 
869  for (keys = (index_atts[4]).sub.value, j = 0; j < (index_atts[4]).sub.count; j++)
870  {
871  key_atts = keys[j].sub.value;
872 
873  if (!DB_IS_NULL (&key_atts[1].value))
874  {
875  id = db_get_int (&key_atts[1].value);
876 
877  for (ids = id_val_p->sub.value, k = 0; k < id_val_p->sub.count; k++)
878  {
879  id_atts = ids[k].sub.value;
880  if (!DB_IS_NULL (&id_atts[0].value) && id == db_get_int (&id_atts[0].value))
881  {
882  pr_clear_value (&key_atts[1].value);
883  pr_clone_value (&id_atts[1].value, &key_atts[1].value);
884  }
885  }
886  }
887  }
888  }
889 
890  catcls_free_or_value (id_val_p);
891  free_and_init (vars);
892 
893  return NO_ERROR;
894 }

938  * catcls_apply_resolutions () -
939  * return:
940  * value(in):
941  * res(in):
942  */
943 static void
944 catcls_apply_resolutions (OR_VALUE * value_p, OR_VALUE * resolution_p)
945 {
946  OR_VALUE *subset_p, *resolution_subset_p;
947  OR_VALUE *attrs, *res_attrs;
948  int i, j;
949  int attr_name_space;
950 
951  for (resolution_subset_p = resolution_p->sub.value, i = 0; i < resolution_p->sub.count; i++)
952  {

956  {

960  * } */
961

969  pr_clear_value (&attrs[3].value);
970  pr_clone_value (&res_attrs[3].value, &attrs[3].value);
971  }
972  }
973  }
974  }

3936 /*

3943  * scan(in):
3944  * force_in_place(in): UPDATE_INPLACE style

3946 static int
3947 catcls_update_instance (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, OR_VALUE * value_p, OID * oid_p, OID * class_oid_p, HFID * hfid_p,
3948  HEAP_SCANCACHE * scan_p, UPDATE_INPLACE_STYLE force_in_place)

3988  {

3990  for (subset_p = attrs[i].sub.value, j = 0; j < attrs[i].sub.count; j++)
3991  {

3995  db_make_oid (&attr_p[0].value, oid_p);

4000  for (k = 1; k < subset_p[j].sub.count; k++)

4017  }
4018  }
4019  else
4020  {

4022  {
4023  uflag = true;
4024  }
4025  }
4026  }
4027

4033  record.area_size = record.length;
4034  record.type = REC_HOME;
4035  record.data = (char *) malloc (record.length);

4041  goto error;

4052  scan_p, NULL) != NO_ERROR)
4053  {
4054  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
4055  error = er_errid ();
4056  goto error;
4057  }
4058 
4059  /* update in place */
4060  heap_create_update_context (&update_context, hfid_p, oid_p, class_oid_p, &record, scan_p, force_in_place);
4061  if (heap_update_logical (thread_p, &update_context) != NO_ERROR)
4062  {
4063  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
4064  error = er_errid ();
4065  goto error;
4066  }
4067 
4068  free_and_init (record.data);
4069  }
4070 
4071  catcls_free_or_value (old_value_p);
4072 
4073  return NO_ERROR;
4074 
4075 error:
4076

4078  {
4079  free_and_init (record.data);
4080  }
4081

4881  heap_scancache_end_modify (thread_p, &scan);

4885  {
